--Run the application

Open terminal in the folder containing main.py and run:

python main.py

OR (recommended way):

uvicorn main:app --reload
What happens here

__name__ == "__main__" means the block runs only when you execute the file directly:

python main.py

reload=True tells Uvicorn to watch for file changes and restart the server automatically.

So if you run:

python main.py

and edit the file → the server reloads automatically.

⚠️ Important detail

If you start the server like this:

uvicorn main:app --reload

Then the if __name__ == "__main__": block does not run at all, because Uvicorn imports the app instead of executing the file.

In that case, Uvicorn handles reload itself.

Recommended practice (most common)

Do not include uvicorn in the code. Just run:

uvicorn main:app --reload

And keep main.py simple:

